HEADWORD: Shortwing
<hw>Short"wing`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any one of several species of small wrenlike Asiatic birds having
short wings and a short tail. They belong to <xex>Brachypterix</xex>,
<xex>Callene</xex>, and allied genera.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

